1.Open Vim and create new file
vim FileName.sh

2.Press Enter
This will open the file in vim editor

3.Press i for insert mode
Now you can start typing

4.Type the Bash script

#!/bin/bash
~
~
echo "Hello wolrd"

5.Press Esc for Exit insert mode

6.Save and Exit Vim

:wq

7.Run the script
sh Filename.sh

output
"Hello world

i-for insert mode

Esc- back to normal mode

:w- for save

:q-for quit

:wq- save and quit


gg-top of the file

shift+g - bottom of the file

shit+o - back line

oo - next line

